[Patient] What can I eat to help with my heart failure? 
[Healthcare Educator] Focus on affordable heart-healthy foods like fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins. 
[Patient] I can't always afford healthy food. Any suggestions? 
[Healthcare Educator] Try buying in bulk, seasonal produce, and canned/frozen fruits and veggies. Also, check out government assistance programs. 
[Patient] Can you give me some examples of budget-friendly meals? 
[Healthcare Educator] How about oatmeal with fruit, a veggie stir-fry with brown rice, or bean soup with whole grain bread? 
[Patient] Thank you for the advice. I'll try to make better food choices. 
[Healthcare Educator] You're welcome. Remember, small changes can make a big difference in managing your heart failure.